<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2018/10/30/spring-cloud-stream-fishtown-rc1-2-1-0-rc1-release-announcement">Spring Cloud Stream Fishtown.RC1 /2.1.0.RC1 Release Announcement</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/b44844c62a496e582a467cf95806ae92?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/olegz">Oleg Zhurakousky</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2018-10-30 15:15:00.0">October 30, 2018</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3458" href="/blog/2018/10/30/spring-cloud-stream-fishtown-rc1-2-1-0-rc1-release-announcement#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>We are pleased to announce the first Release Candidate of the Spring Cloud Stream Fishtown release train - Fishtown.RC1/2.1.0.RC1.</p>
<p>Spring Cloud Stream Fishtown 2.1.0.RC1 is available for use in the <a href="https://repo.spring.io/libs-milestone-local/org/springframework/cloud/spring-cloud-stream/2.1.0.RC1/">Spring Milestone</a> repository. </p>
<p>The following section provides a brief summary of features and improvements included in this release.</p>
<h3><a href="#notable-dependency-upgrades" class="anchor" name="notable-dependency-upgrades"></a>Notable Dependency Upgrades</h3>
<ul>
<li>Spring Boot 2.1.0.RC1</li>
<li>Reactor Californium.RELEASE</li>
<li>Spring Cloud Function 2.1.0.RC1</li>
</ul>
<h3><a href="#spring-cloud-function-support" class="anchor" name="spring-cloud-function-support"></a>Spring Cloud Function support</h3>
<p>The main theme for this release is the introduction of a new programming model which uses <a href="https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-function/">Spring Cloud Function</a> as an alternative for defining <em>stream handlers</em> and <em>sources</em> which can now be expressed as beans of<br> type <code>java.util.function.[Supplier/Function/Consumer]</code></p>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2018/10/30/spring-cloud-stream-fishtown-rc1-2-1-0-rc1-release-announcement">
Read more...
</a>
</article>
